# Cursor Rules for GK Tests Project

## Language
- All code comments must be in English
- All documentation must be in English
- All commit messages should be in English

## Code Style
- Use TypeScript strict mode
- Use meaningful variable and function names
- Add comments for complex logic (in English only)
- Keep functions focused and single-purpose

## Testing
- Use Jest as the testing framework
- Use TypeScript for all test files (*.test.ts)
- Docker containers should be managed using `testcontainers` library
- Always clean up containers in `afterAll` hooks
- Use appropriate timeouts for Docker tests (minimum 60 seconds)
- Prefer sequential test execution to avoid Docker conflicts

## API Testing
- Use native `fetch` API (Node.js 18+) instead of external HTTP clients when possible
- Always handle errors properly in API tests
- Use environment variables for API endpoints

## Project Structure
- Tests go in `tests/` directory
- Utilities go in `utils/` directory
- Test fixtures go in `fixtures/` directory
- **File names use snake_case** (e.g. `sign_csr_to_cert.ts`, `prepare_env.ts`). Entry-point files may stay as `index.ts`.

